turns.content: how many fish are in the sea

It is difficult to say exactly how many fish there are in the sea. There are millions of different species of fish, and the number of individual fish in each species can vary greatly. Additionally, the number of fish in the sea can change over time due to various factors such as overfishing, habitat destruction, and climate change. It is estimated that there are around 200,000 different species of fish in the sea, but the total number of individual fish is likely to be in the billions or trillions.
